My name is Jason Bent, and I am the man behind Bent’s Woodworking. I have spent the last 20 years as an Infantryman in the US Army. During this time, I served as both an ROTC Instructor and a Drill Sergeant. These two jobs were vital to the start of content creation for me as I found a passion for teaching. One topic I find fascinating is shop layout and shop design. Why? Well in the last 6 years I have had 4 different shops and have experimented in more ways than I can count during that time. Because of this, I have learned a great deal about setting up a new space or maximizing an existing space. In my class I hope to share some useful things that I have picked up along the way that will help you in the planning of a new shop, or even uncover ways to maximize your current shop.

Jason Bent is the man behind Bent’s Woodworking. Jason has spent the last 20 years as an Infantryman in the US Army. During that time, he served as both a ROTC Instructor and Drill Sergeant where he found a new passion, teaching. These two jobs were instrumental in his decision to create an instructional woodworking YouTube channel. When he began woodworking, he relied heavily on YouTube himself to get started. In December of 2017 Jason decided he was going to create videos in the hopes that it would help someone else out the way that YouTube had helped him. Now he dedicates his time to making content for others in the hopes that it will make them a better woodworker. Jason will be retiring from the Army in May 2023 and plans to focus all his attention on Bent’s Woodworking.

Thursday was a day I won’t soon forget. I’m currently in Germany visiting my wife’s family. While I was here I had the opportunity to visit @festool and get a tour and some 1 on 1 training with Frank and Georg, Festool’s finest. I got training on the TSV 60, TS 60, CSC, the new reciprocating saw, and the new drills. But, on top of all that, I got to eat lunch with a fantastic group of people, including the owner, Barbara. What an unforgettable day. I can’t believe I have had the opportunities that I have had. #festool #festoolusa #festoolbuiltbetter #festoolcordlesspower #woodworking #bentswoodworking

The added cut capacity, more powerful brushless motor, and the proper blade makes this a perfect option for this task. To top it off, the cut quality is exceptional. This saw is now available in the US. I have a couple videos I will be doing on it in the very near future. #festool #festoolusa #festoolbuiltbetter #tracksaw #bentswoodworking

Over the next few weeks I’ll be focusing on getting organized in my shop. Today, I’m standardizing and organizing my sandpaper. I only use 3M paper now and I couldn’t be happier with it. Hard to believe that a tool packed with so many features is so small and portable allowing me to take it anywhere. Festool’s  new CSC SYS 50 gives you the accuracy and repeatability anywhere you need it thanks to it being cordless. Have you wanted these features at your fingertips outside of your shop? If so, consider adding this machine to your arsenal. Available for shipping September 6th! #festoolfromanywhere #festoolusa #cscsys50 #tablesaw #woodworking #bentswoodworking

I am often asked how I deal with the @3mabrasives 710W Extract net abrasive discs not sticking to the sander. The solution is very simple. This particular type of paper requires what is called a protection pad. This will provide the grip required to securely attach the disc while also protecting your sanding pad leading to longer pad life. To find this paper or protection pads, visit the link in my bio. #3mabrasives #cubitron2 #sandpaper #woodworking #bentswoodworking

It’s amazing how much more efficient you can be with the right tools. Invest in tools that will help with this. Not tools that you think you are “supposed to have” just cause you’re a woodworker.
